<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-282-224  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 282 224.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computergram International  May 23 1989 n1182* Full Text COPYRIGHT Apt Data Services 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>35% go at System Industries. (reduction in workforce)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   System Industries Inc. (layoffs).andO;Ticker:    SYI.andO;Topic:     LayoffFinancial ReportLossesMarketing StrategyComputer Industry.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>35% GO AT SYSTEM INDUSTRIESandM;Taking charges of $11.1m on discontinued operations and $12m forrestructuring against its third quarter figures to leave a net loss for thequarter of $25.9m, System Industries, Milpitas, CA is also cutting its USworkforce by 22%, bringing the reduction to 35% since the start of the fiscalyear.andP;  The integrator of disk subsystems, mainly for DEC users, hopes thatthe measures will enable it to record a profitable fiscal 1990 after threequarters of losses.andP;  The company reports dramatic price erosion and somesoftening in the overall DEC market, and says it expects the trends tocontinue.andP;  The company is to drop many of its product lines, tighten itsfocus on the DEC add-on market, consolidate facilities, cut headquarterscosts and establish new technology and marketing alliances.andO;</TEXT></DOC>